Class Vehicle

  • java.lang.Object
    • fel.cvut.pjv.Vehicle
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    EnemyTank, PlayerTank
    public class Vehicle
extends java.lang.Object
    Parent class of EnemyTank and PlayerTank. Keeps state of vehicles and their position on board.

      • getHit

        public boolean getHit​(ExplosionTile e)
        Method handles hits. Damage is calculated by (explosion_damage/armor)*3. If resulting damage is less than 3 it is set to 3. A hit increments explosion authors score by 100. A kill increments explosion authors score by 500.
        Parameters:
        e - ExplosionTile that hit the vehicle - not null.
        Returns:
        false if vehicle survived hit, true if it got destroyed.
        See Also:
        GameController

      • getDrivenOn

      • getFacingDirection

        public int[] getFacingDirection()
        Gets facing direction of entity. For non-movable entities default value is "up" or {-1,0}.
        Returns:
        {-1,0} means up, {0,1} means right, {1,0} means down, {0,-1} means left.

      • setFacingDirection

        public void setFacingDirection​(int[] direction)
        Sets facing direction of this. Should be only used on entities which can be moved. {-1,0} means up, {0,1} means right, {1,0} means down, {0,-1} means left.
